### HR Candidate Recommendation System - API Requests
### Base URL: http://localhost:18080

### 1. Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/extract/health
Accept: application/json

### 2. Ingest Resume (Golden Path Step 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/resumes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "candidateId": "test_candidate_001",
  "text": "Name: Alex Chen\nEmail: alex.chen@email.com\nLocation: Sydney / Tokyo\nSummary: Backend engineer (Java/Spring) with 4+ years experience..."
}

### 3. Extract Entities (Golden Path Step 2)
# Note: Replace {{documentId}} with the ID returned from resume ingestion
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "documentId": 1,
  "text": "Name: Alex Chen\nEmail: alex.chen@email.com\nLocation: Sydney / Tokyo\nSummary: Backend engineer (Java/Spring) with 4+ years experience...",
  "docType": "RESUME"
}

### 4. Match Resume (Golden Path Step 3)
# Note: Replace {{resumeDocumentId}} with the ID returned from resume ingestion
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/match
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resumeDocumentId": 1,
  "target": "both",
  "roleFilter": null,
  "levelFilter": null
}

### 5. Build Baseline
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/baseline/build?lastN=50&minCount=2
Content-Type: application/json

### 6. Import Success Profile
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/success-profiles/import
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "internal_employee",
  "role": "Java Backend Engineer",
  "level": "mid",
  "company": "Acme Corp",
  "text": "Backend Engineer with 5+ years experience in Java, Spring Boot, PostgreSQL..."
}

### 7. Analyze Resume (Bootstrap)
# Note: Replace {{documentId}} with actual document ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/resumes/{{documentId}}/analyze/bootstrap
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Resume text here..."
}

### 8. Analyze Resume (Baseline)
# Note: Replace {{documentId}} and {{baselineSetId}} with actual IDs
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/resumes/{{documentId}}/analyze/baseline?baselineSetId=1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Resume text here..."
}

### 9. Candidate Stage Management

### 9.1 Get Candidate Info
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/candidates/test_candidate_001
Accept: application/json

### 9.2 Update Candidate Stage (with reasonCode)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/candidates/test_candidate_001/stage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toStage": "screened",
  "changedBy": "hr_user_001",
  "note": "Passed initial screening",
  "reasonCode": "TECH_MISMATCH",
  "jobId": 123,
  "force": false
}

### 9.3 Update Candidate Stage (without reasonCode)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/candidates/test_candidate_002/stage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toStage": "shortlisted",
  "changedBy": "hr_user_002",
  "note": "Candidate looks promising",
  "reasonCode": null,
  "jobId": null,
  "force": false
}

### 9.4 Update Candidate Stage to Rejected (with reasonCode)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/candidates/test_candidate_001/stage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toStage": "rejected",
  "changedBy": "hr_user_001",
  "note": "Final rejection: salary expectations mismatch",
  "reasonCode": "SALARY",
  "jobId": 123,
  "force": true
}

### 9.5 Get Candidate Stage History
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/candidates/test_candidate_001/stage/history
Accept: application/json

### 9.6 Test Various Reason Codes

# TECH_MISMATCH
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/candidates/test_reason_001/stage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toStage": "rejected",
  "changedBy": "hr_user_001",
  "note": "Technical skills mismatch",
  "reasonCode": "TECH_MISMATCH",
  "jobId": 456,
  "force": true
}

# SALARY
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/candidates/test_reason_002/stage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toStage": "rejected",
